    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential NULL dereference and buffer overflow in encode_ng_handover_required\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_ng_handover_required` function in `ngap_gNB_mobility_management.c` had several potential issues that could lead to crashes or undefined behavior. This fix addresses NULL pointer dereferences, array bounds violations, and improper error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_mobility_management.c`: \n  - Added input validation for NULL message and source2target pointers\n  - Fixed array indexing to prevent out-of-bounds access when processing PDU sessions\n  - Replaced AssertFatal calls with proper error handling that returns NULL on failure\n  - Added proper memory cleanup in error paths to prevent memory leaks\n  - Fixed format specifiers to match the original code\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be reproduced by calling `encode_ng_handover_required` with:\n1. A NULL message pointer - would previously cause a segmentation fault\n2. A message with NULL source2target field - would previously cause a segmentation fault  \n3. Mismatched array sizes between nb_of_pdusessions and source2target->nb_pdu_session_resource - could cause buffer overflow\n4. ASN.1 encoding failures - would previously terminate the program instead of returning an error\n\nThese conditions could occur during handover procedures when the network is under stress or receiving malformed messages from the UE.\n"
}